<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-12-01 - Release of 88&#176; C (190&#176; F) Coolant Thermostat</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi981201" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>98-12-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>January, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Release of 88&#176; C (190&#176; F) Coolant Thermostat</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>DT 466</engfam>
                <engfam>530</engfam>
                <engfam>DT 466E</engfam>
                <engfam>530E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A new thermostat is released starting with serial number 1082180 and above.</para>
                <para>The new thermostat provides a higher engine coolant temperature during extended idling and cold
                    weather operation. The thermostat begins to open at 88&#176; C (190&#176; F) and is fully open at
                    100&#176; C (212&#176; F) as opposed to the current thermostat that begins to open at 82&#176; C
                    (180&#176; F). In addition, the new thermostat improves emissions output at low power ratings.
                </para>
                <para>The new thermostat replaces the prior thermostat for all applications. When using the new 88&#176;
                    C (190&#176; F) thermostat on prior model year engines, it should be noted that the engine operating
                    temperature will be slightly higher
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
